{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a0a29735-38b7-425a-8023-761c2a4cbb42","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with the reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5b48c98f-94a8-460d-b129-05bd6d78d113","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to look anything up.","outputTokens":351,"requestId":"E3C0:2CBD0C:179A046:1A53715:6A052396"},"id":"faf55660-db0d-4e80-8310-0028dd2206fe","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:34.872Z","parentId":"3dec8775-323c-4131-b76d-ef28a36a4388"}
